</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">First aid training in the early years is crucial for compliance with health and safety regulations and for the peace of mind, it brings to staff and parents. Knowing that educators and carers can competently handle medical emergencies can significantly impact the care and safety of children.




















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-33_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics
</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-35_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">According to data from the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), over 15,000 injuries were reported in educational settings in the UK last year alone. Many of these involved young children and could have been mitigated with prompt first aid response.




















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid </strong>- The immediate assistance given to any person suffering from either a minor or serious illness or injury, with care provided to preserve life, prevent the condition from worsening, or promote recovery.



































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early years setting</strong> - Any environment that provides education and care to children from birth to five years old, including nurseries, preschools, and childminders.




































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-46_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-47_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-48_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-50_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The importance of first aid in early years is underscored by various legislative frameworks and guidelines:
























</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-52_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 </strong>- These regulations require employers to provide adequate and appropriate equipment, facilities, and personnel to ensure employees receive immediate attention if they are injured or taken ill at work.




































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) framework </strong>- This framework mandates that at least one person with a current paediatric first aid certificate must be on the premises when children are present.




































